  "text": "The CSS layout engine reflow pipeline in Mozilla Firefox consists of three major components:\n\n1. **Frame Construction**: The process begins in `layout/base/nsCSSFrameConstructor.cpp/h`, which implements nsFrameConstructor. This component traverses the DOM tree and constructs a parallel frame tree. Each DOM element is represented by one or more layout frames that handle size, positioning, and painting.\n\n2. **Block Layout Reflow**: The core block layout algorithm is implemented in several files:\n   - `layout/generic/BlockReflowState.cpp/h`: Maintains reflow state for block-level layout, including constraint information and available space calculations\n   - `layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.cpp/h`: Implements the main block frame class (nsBlockFrame), which handles the layout of block-level content\n   - `layout/generic/nsBlockReflowContext.cpp/h`: Provides context-specific reflow operations for block content\n   - `layout/generic/nsInlineFrame.cpp/h` and `layout/generic/nsLineLayout.cpp/h`: Handle inline content layout, which integrates with block layout\n   - `layout/generic/nsTextFrame.cpp/h`: Implements text layout as part of the inline layout system\n\n3. **Dirty Frame Invalidation Mechanism**: The invalidation system marks frames as needing reflow and updates the display list:\n   - `layout/generic/nsFrameState.cpp/h` and `layout/generic/nsFrameStateBits.h`: Define frame state bits that track whether a frame is dirty or needs reflow\n   - `layout/base/PresShell.cpp/h`: The presentation shell orchestrates the reflow process, scheduling layout and managing the dirty frame list\n   - `layout/base/nsPresContext.cpp/h`: Maintains presentation context and coordinates between style system and layout\n   - `layout/base/nsFrameManager.cpp/h`: Manages frame tree operations and maintains frame state\n   - `layout/painting/nsDisplayListInvalidation.cpp/h`: Handles invalidation of display list items when content changes\n   - `layout/painting/RetainedDisplayListBuilder.cpp/h`: Rebuilds display lists incrementally, only invalidating changed regions\n   - `layout/base/nsRefreshDriver.cpp/h`: Coordinates reflow and paint operations with the refresh cycle\n\n**Reflow Infrastructure**: The reflow process uses:\n   - `layout/generic/ReflowInput.cpp/h`: Input parameters for reflow (constraints, available space, writing mode)\n   - `layout/generic/ReflowOutput.cpp/h`: Output from reflow (actual dimensions, baseline information)\n   - `layout/base/nsIReflowCallback.h`: Callbacks for post-reflow processing\n\n**Core Frame Types**: The implementation includes:\n   - `layout/generic/nsIFrame.cpp/h`: Base interface for all frame objects\n   - `layout/generic/nsContainerFrame.cpp/h`: Base class for frames with children\n   - `layout/generic/nsLeafFrame.cpp/h`: Base class for frames without children\n   - `layout/generic/ViewportFrame.cpp/h`: Root frame for the viewport\n   - Specialized frames: `nsPageFrame`, `nsGridContainerFrame`, `nsFlexContainerFrame`, `ScrollContainerFrame`, table frames, etc.\n\n**Display List and Painting**: The invalidation system integrates with painting through:\n   - `layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp/h`: Maintains the display list (sequence of paint operations)\n   - `layout/base/FrameProperties.h`: Stores auxiliary frame data\n   - `layout/base/DepthOrderedFrameList.cpp/h`: Tracks frames in depth order for proper reflow/invalidation\n\nThe reflow pipeline follows these steps: (1) Mark frames as dirty when content changes, (2) Schedule reflow during the refresh cycle in PresShell, (3) Traverse the frame tree and call Reflow() on each frame, (4) Update the display list, (5) Invalidate changed regions for painting. This architecture ensures efficient incremental layout and rendering updates."
